      "body": {
        "type": "TextualBody",
        "value": "The use of a low-angle shot on the policeman and a high-angle shot on the wagoner conveys a power dynamic of the exchange. The low-angle shot makes the policeman seem menacing and powerful, while the high-angle shot makes Borom Sarret seem weak and subordinate to the policeman. It is worth noting, however, Borom's face is defiant which suggests a challenge to the policeman's authority.",
        "format": "text/plain",
        "purpose": "commenting"
      },
      "target": {
