        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": {
        "type": "TextualBody",
        "value": "Borom Sarret comments depressingly about how a traffic light automatically applies the stringent constrains of society. The light controls whether he may go or must stop, constricting his movements. He laments \"it's a prison\" and \"that's modern life,\" which indicates a past, less constraining society. This is likely frustration towards colonization of Senegal.",
        "format": "text/plain",
        "purpose": "commenting"
      },
      "target": {
        "source": {
